    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nUsers must remember the server address to use `--server` or `:connect`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIt should be easy to reattach after detach.\n\n- `:connect` without args shows a menu of servers. \n- `serverlist({info=true})` returns info used to build the `:connect` menu.\n\nThe end goal is for the serverlist to be useful/intuitive so that users can choose their intended target without having to remember obscure addresses. The general shape is:\n\n```\n[server-name] [last-activity] [possibly-other-info]\n```\n\nwhere \n- [x] `[last-activity]` is a relative timestamp of the most-recent *user activity* (this might require a new feature like `v:useractive`, not sure). https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39423\n- [ ] `[server-name]` initially will be [this](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/682067c46a7e053270fceb3e498aea4083d4d9c9/src/nvim/log.c#L304-L305), or maybe a truncated version of `v:servername`\n     - but later we will introduce `v:name` or [v:serverid](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/1758)\n\nso for example,\n\n```\nnvim.12345.0  3 minutes ago\nnvim.56869.0  5 hours ago\n```\n\n",
